cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with generating 3D stereoscopic content from a single image, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and deep learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a large dataset of stereoscopic images, which could also place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
